105.472.  Violation of law — complaint — oath. — 1.  The office of state courts administrator shall collect information related to the filing and disposition of petitions to certify juveniles pursuant to section 211.071.
  2.  The data collected pursuant to this section shall include the following:
  (1)  The number of certification petitions filed annually;
  (2)  The disposition of certification petitions filed annually;
  (3)  The offenses for which certification petitions are filed annually;
  (4)  The race of the juveniles for whom the certification petitions are filed annually; and
  (5)  The number of juveniles who have waived their right to counsel.
  3.  The data collected pursuant to this section shall be made publicly available annually.
(L. 2024 S.B. 754, et al.)
